flowchart TB
    N1["1. neo-execution-core: Proof/evidence flow shows how a claim becomes checkable."]
    N2["2. Claim: This unit performed: Validate batch shape | Apply deterministic transition | Commit new state root."]
    N3["3. Witness or input: L2 batch | previous state root | execution parameters"]
    N4["4. Execution or check: execute deterministic rules and produce checkable output"]
    N5["5. Public commitment: input digest, transition digest, and output digest"]
    N6["6. Verifier: neo-zkvm-guest | neo-zkvm-host | gateway services"]
    N7["7. Accepted result: execution trace | new state root | public proof inputs"]
    N8["8. Rejected result: reject output and retain diagnostics"]
    N1 --> N2
    N2 --> N3
    N3 --> N4
    N4 --> N5
    N5 --> N6
    N6 --> N7
    N7 --> N8
    classDef core fill:#0f172a,stroke:#38bdf8,color:#e5f2ff,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef support fill:#111827,stroke:#64748b,color:#f8fafc;
    class N1 core;
    class N2,N3,N4,N5,N6,N7,N8 support;
